---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import { site, mailLink } from '../data/site';
---
<Layout
  current=""
  title="Cookie Policy | The London Left Hand Drive Centre"
  description="How the London LHD Centre uses cookies and how to manage your preferences."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Cookie Policy"
    subtitle="How we use cookies on this site."
    crumb="Cookie Policy"
  />

  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="legal-prose fade-in">
        <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 02/06/2026</p>

        <p>
          This Cookie Policy explains how {site.name} (“we”, “us”, “our”) uses cookies and
          similar technologies on this website, and the choices available to you. It should be read
          alongside our Privacy Policy. This site is designed to be light-touch: by default it does
          not set any tracking or advertising cookies.
        </p>

        <h2>What are cookies?</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you visit a website. They are
          widely used to make websites work, to make them work more efficiently, and to provide
          information to the site owner. Cookies can be “session” cookies, which are deleted when you
          close your browser, or “persistent” cookies, which remain until they expire or are deleted.
        </p>
        <p>
          Similar technologies — such as your browser’s <strong>localStorage</strong> — can also
          store small amounts of information on your device. Where we mention “cookies” in this
          policy, we mean cookies and these comparable technologies.
        </p>

        <h2>The cookies we use</h2>
        <p>
          This is a static website. Out of the box, it sets <strong>no tracking, analytics or
          advertising cookies</strong>, and it does not profile you or follow you across other sites.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Your consent choice (localStorage).</strong> When you respond to our consent
            banner, your preference is saved locally in your browser using localStorage so that we
            don’t ask you again on every page. This is a strictly necessary preference used only to
            remember your choice — it is not a tracking cookie, is not shared with anyone, and never
            leaves your device.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Optional analytics (consent only).</strong> We do not run analytics by default.
            Should we ever introduce analytics in future, any such cookies would be set
            <strong>only after you have given your consent</strong> through the banner, and you would
            be able to withdraw that consent at any time.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Third-party content</h2>
        <p>
          Some pages embed content from third parties, which may set their own cookies once that
          content loads. In particular, our contact and locations pages include
          <strong>Google Maps</strong> embeds that show our Barnes and Chelsea Harbour showrooms.
          When a map loads, Google may set cookies on your device. These cookies are controlled by
          Google rather than by us, and are governed by Google’s own privacy and cookie policies.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you would prefer not to allow these cookies, you can avoid loading the embedded maps and
          instead use the “Get directions” links to open Google Maps in a separate tab, or adjust
          your browser settings as described below.
        </p>

        <h2>Managing cookies</h2>
        <p>You can control and manage cookies in two main ways:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Our on-site consent banner.</strong> When you first visit, our banner lets you
            accept or decline non-essential cookies. Because your choice is stored locally, you can
            change your mind by clearing your browser’s site data for this website, which will prompt
            the banner to appear again.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Your browser settings.</strong> Most browsers let you view, block or delete
            cookies, and refuse cookies from specific sites. Please note that blocking strictly
            necessary cookies or clearing site data may affect how parts of this website function.
            You can find guidance in your browser’s help pages.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes to the site, to the
          technologies we use, or to legal and regulatory requirements. Any changes will be posted on
          this page with a revised “Last updated” date above.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Cookie Policy or how we handle cookies, please contact
          us at <a href={mailLink}>{site.email}</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
